The paper discusses the use of Gaussian processes in machine learning and signal processing, which are both relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also specifically mentions signal processing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SP (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper discusses recursive and adaptive algorithms, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses non-Gaussian noise models and classification scenarios, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
